      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 363: congestionCallback_ is written under mutex_ in setCongestionCallback() but read and invoked here without synchronization. If the callback is configured or cleared while RTCP processing runs, this is a data race on std::function. Copy the callback under the same mutex, then invoke the copy outside the lock to avoid both the race and re-entrant locking issues.\n```suggestion\nstd::function\u003cvoid(float)\u003e congestionCallback;\n{\n    std::lock_guard lock(mutex_);\n    congestionCallback \u003d congestionCallback_;\n}\nif (pondLoss \u003e\u003d AUDIO_CONGESTION_THRESHOLD \u0026\u0026 congestionCallback) {\n    JAMI_LOG(\"[AudioQoS] Audio congestion detected (loss: {}%), signaling video to reduce bitrate\", pondLoss);\n    congestionCallback(pondLoss);\n}\n```",
      "revId": "5ab20db455e57bc0c4f0a98f6e3543f86b50e493",
